#: src/influences.md:1
msgid "Influences"
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:3
msgid "This page explains how Redox was influenced by other operating systems."
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:5
msgid "(The list is ordered by influence level)"
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:7
msgid "[Minix](https://minix3.org/)"
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:9
msgid ""
"The most influential Unix-like system with a microkernel. It has advanced "
"features such as system modularity, [kernel panic](https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/Kernel_panic) resistence, driver reincarnation, protection against bad "
"drivers and secure interfaces for [process comunication](https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Inter-process_communication)."
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:11
msgid ""
"Redox is largely influenced by Minix - it has a similar architecture but "
"with a feature set written in Rust."
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:13
msgid "[How Minix influenced the Redox design](./microkernels.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:15
msgid "[seL4](https://sel4.systems/)"
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:17
msgid "The most performant and simplest microkernel of the world."
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:19
msgid ""
"Redox follow the same principle, trying to make the kernel-space small as "
"possible (moving components to user-space and reducing the number of system "
"calls, passing the complexity to user-space) and keeping the overall "
"performance good (reducing the context switch cost)."
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:21
msgid "[Plan 9](http://9p.io/plan9/index.html)"
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:23
msgid ""
"This Bell Labs OS brings the concept of \"Everything is a File\" to the "
"highest level, doing all the system communication from the filesystem."
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:25
msgid ""
"[Drew DeVault explains the Plan 9](https://drewdevault.com/2022/11/12/In-"
"praise-of-Plan-9.html)"
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:26
msgid "[Plan 9's influence on Redox](./schemes-resources.md)"
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:28
msgid "[Linux](https://www.kernel.org/)"
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:30
msgid ""
"The most advanced monolithic kernel and biggest open-source project of the "
"world. It brought several improvements and optimizations to the Unix-like "
"world."
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:32
msgid ""
"Redox tries to implement the Linux performance improvements in a microkernel "
"design."
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:34
msgid "[BSD](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Berkeley_Software_Distribution)"
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:36
msgid ""
"This Unix [family](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research_Unix) included "
"several improvements on Unix systems and the open-source variants of BSD "
"added many improvements to the original system (like Linux did)."
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:38
msgid ""
"[FreeBSD](https://www.freebsd.org/) - The [Capsicum](https://man.freebsd.org/"
"cgi/man.cgi?capsicum(4)) (a capability-based system) and [jails](https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Freebsd_jail) (a sandbox technology) influenced the Redox "
"namespaces implementation."
msgstr ""

#: src/influences.md:40
msgid ""
"[OpenBSD](https://www.openbsd.org/) - The [system call](https://man.openbsd."
"org/pledge.2), [filesystem](https://man.openbsd.org/unveil.2), [display "
"server](https://www.xenocara.org/) and [audio server](https://man.openbsd."
"org/sndiod.8) sandbox and [others](https://www.openbsd.org/innovations.html) "
"influenced the Redox security."
msgstr ""
